  "records": {
    "description": "The Aeternum SMP storage system was designed as a middle ground between a standard storage system and an encoded one, aiming to be easy to build and use. It includes all the essentials that anyone might need from a storage system, with a strong focus on practicality and reliability.",
    "features": [
      "Regular Version 97.44% Hopper Locking - Essential Version 98.70% Hopper Locking",
      "1.7 MSPT idle, 3 MSPT active (Ryzen 9 7950X3D with Lithium 1.21.4)",
      "744 chest hall items, one chest per item",
      "248 external bulk items, 0.95 million capacity per item",
      "7 multi-item categories",
      "Unstackable sorter + encoder",
      "Set-based unloading array",
      "Some peripherals (furnace array, brewer, mass crafter, box dyer, restock display)",
      "System status panel",
      "Basic error checking, which can pause the input if there is a problem."
    ],
    "notes": "By Lukeem, Juthons, LuisitoLapapa , and Danc04 . See thread for full credits, additional information, and world download/schematic."
